<!DOCTYPE html SYSTEM "http://www.thymeleaf.org/dtd/xhtml1-strict-thymeleaf-4.dtd">

<html xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml" xmlns:th="http://www.thymeleaf.org" lang="en">
<head th:replace="header.thyme::head('Book Shelf', 'Explore notes taken from books about software development')"></head>
<body onload="prettyPrint()">

<div id="wrap">
    <div th:replace="menu.thyme::menu"></div>

    <div class="container">

        <div class="mt-5 text-center">
            <h1>Book Shelf</h1>
        </div>

        <div>
            <p>
                This is a collection of books I have either read, or intend to read. I usually take notes from those
                I've read already. These notes are listed in a dedicated page for each of the books listed below and
                are intended to be used as a memo for myself.
            </p>
            <p>
                They are publicly available because I think many people may find them useful as a summary or as a
                reading list to be considered, but, if you want to really learn about these topics, you should read the
                linked books.
            </p>
            <p>
                <strong>Disclaimer</strong>: the content here is not intended to be used as an official reference.
            </p>

            <small>
                If you're the co/author, publisher (in general, a copyright owner) of some of these books and consider
                the content of this website (https://lealceldeiro.com/) doesn't comply with your work's copyright
                policy, please get in touch through:
                <a href="mailto:asiel@lealceldeiro.com?subject=About%20use%20of%20book%20in%20your%20Blog%20(Legal%20Notice)&body=Hi%2C%20Asiel%2C%0A%0AI%27m%20writing%20you%20in%20regards%20to%20the%20use%20you%27ve%20made%20in%20your%20blog%20of%20the%20book%20titled%3A%20">
                    asiel@lealceldeiro.com
                </a>.
            </small>
        </div>

        <div class="vstack gap-3">
            <th:block th:each="note, stat : ${all_content}">
                <div class="p-2" th:if="${#strings.equals(note.type, config.booknote_key)}">
                    <a th:href="*{content.rootpath + note.uri}" class="link-underline link-underline-opacity-0">

                        <div class="card mt-3" style="max-width: 30em;">
                            <div class="row g-0">
                                <div class="col-md-4">
                                    <img class="img-fluid rounded-start"
                                         th:src="${note.imageSrc}"
                                         th:alt="${note.imageAlt}">
                                </div>
                                <div class="col-md-8">
                                    <div class="card-body">
                                        <h5 class="card-title" th:text="${note.title}"></h5>
                                        <p class="card-text" th:text="${note.authors}"></p>
                                        <p class="card-text">
                                            <small class="text-body-secondary" th:text="'Published: ' + ${note.published}"></small>
                                        </p>
                                    </div>
                                </div>
                            </div>
                        </div>

                    </a>
                </div>
            </th:block>
        </div>
    </div>

</div>

<div th:replace="footer.thyme::footer"></div>

<script th:with="rootpath=(${content.rootpath != null} ? ${content.rootpath} : '')"
        th:src="${rootpath} + 'js/base.js'"></script>
</body>
</html>
